Sentencas: The cathodic reaction mechanism of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) was investigated for an electrode-electrolyte system of Lao(0.6)Ba(0.4)CoO(3) (LBC)-BaCeO(3), under both the O(2-) conducting and H(+)/O(2-) mixed-ionic conducting conditions.
Titulo: La0.6Ba0.4CoO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells using a BaCeO3 electrolyte

Sentencas: AC impedance measurements were carried out, and the electrode interfacial conductivities were calculated.
Titulo: La0.6Ba0.4CoO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells using a BaCeO3 electrolyte

Sentencas: The experimental results revealed that the processes dominating the electrode resistance for the O(2-) conducting and the H(+)/O(2-) mixed-ionic conducting conditions are different.
Titulo: La0.6Ba0.4CoO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells using a BaCeO3 electrolyte

Sentencas: It was also found that the process dominating the electrode resistance changes at 700 degrees C under H(+)/O(2-) mixed-ionic conducting conditions.
Titulo: La0.6Ba0.4CoO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells using a BaCeO3 electrolyte

Sentencas: The process dominating the electrode resistance above 700 degrees C is Postulated to be the reaction O(LBC) +
Titulo: La0.6Ba0.4CoO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells using a BaCeO3 electrolyte
